<p> 
Today we have Printer Cat, who we ran into in the CIT.
We aksed Printer Cat what she was up to. Response: <blockquote>"I'm in your printer, nomming your papers."</blockquote>

When asked for more details, she replied:


<blockquote>"People always yell at me for nomming their papers, but they don't stop and consider what it's like to have no 
higher purpose besides wood pulp consumption. Sometimes it all feels so meaningless. When I'm feeling especially 
empty, I go to the art supply store and nom on some fancy papers. That usually makes me feel better."</blockquote>

On our way back to headquarters, we ran into Tech Support Kitty hanging out near the MSLab. 
</p>
