<div class = "techKitty">
<p>
Tech Kitty told us that tech support was just her after-school job; during the day she is a computer science student. 
When she graduates, her dream job is to work for Google.
She wants to move to either California or New York City, but for now she lives in Providence with her family. 
We asked her what she thought about CS.

<blockquote>"Computer science is super cool. There's plenty of programming, but what I really enjoy is problem solving. 
It's hard to pick one specific subject because there are so many different applications. 
In the CS department alone I've taken classes on computer graphics, math, robotics, and biology and I learned cool stuff in all of them."</blockquote>

At that point, Tech Kitty had to respond to an issue with the fourth-floor printers, so we said goodbye.
</p>
